A good app for those needing a software catalog for Western releases, but falls short on hardware collection, import games, and other factors regarding title value (unopened, opened but complete, etc.) Not being able to add, for example, a Japanese Sega Saturn or a note that you have an extra NES to your list seems like an oversight and a missed opportunity for collectors. Edit/update: value of items can be manually adjusted for condition, import titles can be submitted, notes can be added. OK.

It's definitely helped me to catalog and organize my games! Love this app! Only small complaint is the filter doesn't seem to work when I try to take certain labels off. Other than that, highly recommend!
replyContent: Hey David. Sorry to hear about the issue with the filter. Would you mind reaching out to me via email with some more details so I can fix it? Thanks!

It has potential to be even better though.. some suggestions that would make me enjoy it even more;  - Track games I'm currently playing (You can currently track played or beat but not playing) - Save what platforms I own so that each time I search I don't have to keep refining the filters - Profiles so that I can also manage from a browser too.. - Game suggestions based on my collection  - Badges or trophies.. basically gamifying it a bit.. for example if I've added 5 games to my collection I receive a badge or trophy as a noob for example.. then if I add 100 games I  get a badge or trophy saying border etc.   That's just some suggestions that would make me enjoy the app even more so.
